Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her disheveled hair hung over her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her body looked limp and powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl's blazing eyes stared at her across the room from under half-closed eyelids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.87,0:15:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed! In this very Kamiyama High,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was once a pianist, who on the eve of the national competition—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.38,0:15:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.42,0:15:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno. There could well have been, but I don't know anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.72,0:15:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't often see you staying so late after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usually, you remember to do your homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.52,0:16:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}did{\i0} do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just forgot to bring it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.56,0:16:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that I have to write the same essay all over again while listening to you blabber on about nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, they say there really is a ghost with disheveled hair somewhere in the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.37,0:16:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Class A talking about it during lunch break.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.12,0:16:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now all that matters is how the rumor will spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.04,0:16:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The second of Kamiyama High's seven wonders!" Or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.50,0:16:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also interested to see how long it'll take for it to reach me in Class D.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.92,0:16:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a minute. Who did you hear that from? And where?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.43,0:16:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda told me a little while ago, in the clubroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.81,0:16:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it could be the second wonder. So there's already a first?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Can you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.32,0:16:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So here's where you two were!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I filled out the paperwork, Fukube.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.79,0:17:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. As a member of the Student Council, I've got to put you through some red tape as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.04,0:17:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.92,0:17:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I was the one who agreed to be club president.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You got here at just the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.09,0:17:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi just told me about this weird rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.68,0:17:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that! During lunch break—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about the secret club. Did you know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.14,0:17:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The secret club?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.77,0:17:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, tell her please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.65,0:17:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen closely. I'll tell you all about the secret club, and the controversy surrounding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it from the other council members.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.37,0:17:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The school has lots of clubs,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.16,0:17:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so there are always lots of recruitment posters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.54,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the school's bulletin boards are usually filled with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.96,0:17:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the council finds unauthorized posters, we remove them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.51,0:17:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.72,0:18:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's always one mysterious poster that doesn't belong to any club, but it shows up every single year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.35,0:18:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, it was just the time and place for a meeting, written on a scrap of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There seems to be a secret club outside the authority of the council,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,covertly recruiting new members.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:15.40,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fax0.03\blur0.6\fnFrom Where You Are\c&H182020&\frz354.1\pos(666,77)}Diligence Deter{\c&H25312F&}m{\c&H303E3C&}i{\c&H354342&}n{\c&H414E4D&}a{\c&H465353&}t{\c&H4A5959&}i{\c&H485858&}o{\c&H495555&}n
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.77,0:18:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what they do or who they are, but they exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.78,0:18:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.90,0:18:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their name is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Golden Web.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Golden Web...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year Tanabe, president of the Student Council, tried to make contact with them after seeing their poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.04,0:18:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They concluded that it was just a prank, given the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.59,0:18:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.42,0:18:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.59,0:18:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the day of the graduation ceremony, one of the graduates told Tanabe:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.76,0:18:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was the president of the Golden Web.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.02,0:18:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take good care of the next president as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you can find him, that is."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:18:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they're recruiting this year as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, we haven't found any posters yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A single recruitment poster...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.41,0:19:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the Golden Web.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop thinking about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.58,0:19:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.29,0:19:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.71,0:19:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I said that you'd arrived at just the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.04,0:19:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.21,0:19:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we're going to look for that poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.13,0:19:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.59,0:19:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are thirty bulletin boards altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lot... Are we going to check them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.81,0:19:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.64,0:19:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be faster if we worked out the most likely place beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.98,0:19:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think it'd be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were them, I'd put it in some out-of-the-way place where it wasn't too noticeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're missing the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.49,0:19:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.95,0:19:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there really is a poster, then it'll be on the bulletin board in front of the main entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.08,0:19:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's the most conspicuous place it could be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou's probably on to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at all these posters again, this school never fails to impress me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.72,0:20:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,India Ink Club, Manga Lab, Track & Field and Basketball teams...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no end to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Oreki?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just overwhelmed by the combined enthusiasm of everyone who drew these posters...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.78,0:20:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's entirely beyond the understanding of a low-energy person like you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the bulletin board that the first-year students see as soon as they arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a real battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.25,0:20:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A battlefield?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! With this many posters, the unauthorized ones would just blend in!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.17,0:20:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's also true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.88,0:20:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.92,0:20:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a look at the board to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.84,0:20:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.59,0:20:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Global Theater, the Debate Circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.14,0:20:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We even have a 100 Poets Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.47,0:20:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the Fortunetelling Lab!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.81,0:20:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My friend joined that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Composers' Club, Table Tennis, Art Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see the Golden Web's poster anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't expect to recognize it immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably have some trick to avoid being noticed by the council.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it's here, I'm sure we'll find it sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.21,0:21:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.59,0:21:28.34,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\pos(0,0)\bord0\blur0.5\p1\c&H878F92&}m 470 286 l 496 425 l 854 343 l 802 223 l 658 249 l 654 251 l 650 252 l 647 254 l 631 260
Dialogue: 1,0:21:26.59,0:21:28.34,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\blur0.7\fnJDVega\frz11.181\pos(651,270)\c&H31373A&}The Golden Web\NTwo members needed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.64,0:21:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.26,0:21:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it'd be in a more secluded place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.48,0:21:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how a first-year student would think.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more inexperienced you are, the more you want to show off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you were clever enough to run a secret club, you'd try to outwit people in a more dignified way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.69,0:21:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.82,0:21:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.45,0:21:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you put it that way, it's pretty obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'm not surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.78,0:21:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, this is an unauthorized poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.37,0:21:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I gotta do my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.79,0:21:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.96,0:22:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to turn in my essay at the staff room then go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.55,0:22:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll head home too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.26,0:22:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's say goodbye here for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.64,0:22:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more inexperienced you are, the more you want to show off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.89,0:22:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the best way to tame a mystery is with another mystery.{same as "diamonds cut diamonds" ...を以って...を制す}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.02,0:22:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.23,0:22:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.57,0:22:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just knew she'd show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.32,0:22:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you made that note and pinned it to the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.87,0:22:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it worked out pretty well in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.45,0:22:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would you go so far as to turn a simple mystery into something so grand?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.04,0:22:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not because she's no match for you in that regard, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the music room was too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.55,0:22:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.43,0:22:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.97,0:22:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to go past the main entrance, hand in my essay at the staff room and go straight home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.60,0:23:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.85,0:23:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're you, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.65,0:23:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop thinking about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.15,0:23:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What I have to do, I do quickly."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.36,0:23:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou, that won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.99,0:23:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should recite your motto with your head held high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.25,0:23:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way you said it just then sounded like a mere excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.17,0:23:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best way to tame a mystery is with another mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.22,0:23:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.01,0:23:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good breaking ball.{baseball term}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.47,0:23:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, Houtarou,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.80,0:23:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's not the way you do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.89,0:23:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Chitanda showed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.60,0:23:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why didn't you just tell her that you didn't know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was your first mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.07,0:23:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been able to just turn people down until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.90,0:23:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.24,0:23:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The more inexperienced you are, the more you want to show off."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.33,0:23:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That fits you perfectly today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:24:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not used to being around her at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.29,0:24:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that's why you sorted things out in such a roundabout way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.59,0:24:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may have just wanted to reject her,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.51,0:24:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.92,0:24:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to do no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.30,0:24:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.09,0:24:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just wanted to hold on to the status quo.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.39,0:24:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So I'm just holding on...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.52,0:24:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think about mystery of the music room, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.11,0:24:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her hair was messy and her eyes were half closed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as if she just woke up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.57,0:24:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.33,0:24:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pianist was sleepy, so she took a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.99,0:24:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She put on the Moonlight Sonata to play so that she would wake up before the school closed at six.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.96,0:24:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.13,0:24:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I suppose that explains it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.88,0:24:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, the CD player would probably still be set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.88,0:24:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the music room is too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.93,0:24:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.47,0:24:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.35,0:25:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get the feeling that going there would've cost you less energy in the long run.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.77,0:25:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might be all right today,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.35,0:25:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it could cost you more in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.36,0:25:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.61,0:25:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about owing me anything for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.66,0:25:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.21,0:25:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holding on, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.84,0:25:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Activities of the esteemed Classics Club
